      "writtenOn": "2010-11-09T10:49:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suggest using socket_address_list_create(host, NULL, 0) to convert the parameter to a list of SockAddresses that you will be able to test sequentially. This will allow you to specify any hostname (not only \"localhost\" + IP address). \n\nSee \"sockets.h\" for the function declaration. Note that this is really a portable wrapper around getaddrinfo() (http://linux.die.net/man/3/getaddrinfo)",
      "revId": "1b604aaf481c72652136033523db7d916b3e9d69",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
