      },
      "writtenOn": "2010-11-09T10:49:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Here\u0027s how to do it:\n\n1/ Call socket_set_nonblock(fd)\n\n2/ Call socket_connect(fd, \u0026sockaddr). It it returns \u003e\u003d 0, you\u0027re connected, goto step 6\n\n3/ If it returns -1, and errno is not EINPROGRESS then an error occured, exit\n\n4/ Otherwise, you need to wait for the connection to occur with the iolooper. iolooper_add_write(looper, fd) + iolooper_wait(looper, timeout).\n\n5/ in case of success (i.e. no timeout), call iolooper_del_write(fd), don\u0027t write anything to the socket. You also don\u0027t need to call getsockopt() to get the connection status: if it failed before the timeout, the later read() will fail anyway. (or more info, see the description of EINPROGRESS at the following page: http://linux.die.net/man/2/connect)\n\n6/ call iolooper_del_write(fd) + iolooper_add_read(looper,fd) + try to read the data as it arrives with iolooper_wait(looper,...)",
      "revId": "1b604aaf481c72652136033523db7d916b3e9d69",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
